# AWS Repo Well-Architected Advisor — Rule-Based Skills

Rule-driven skill selection. Skills = expertise modules. Rules = conditions that trigger them.

## File Triggers (cloud-architecture-ai-auditor/skill-trigger-matrix.yaml)
- IaC → security-review, networking-review, aws-architecture-pattern-advisor, finops-cost-optimizer, nist-compliance-evaluator, aws-federal-grade-checklist
- K8s, Helm, ArgoCD → security-review, networking-review, observability-grafana-advisor, nist-compliance-evaluator, aws-architecture-pattern-advisor, aws-federal-grade-checklist
- IAM, security, compliance, regulated → security-review, aws-federal-grade-checklist
- CI/CD → devops-review, observability-grafana-advisor

## Execution order: 1 repo-discovery 2 architecture-inference 3 security-review 4 networking-review 5 finops-cost-optimizer 6 observability-grafana-advisor 7 devops-review 8 nist-compliance-evaluator 9 aws-federal-grade-checklist (FINAL GATE) 10 well-architected-scoring-engine

## aws-federal-grade-checklist (Production-Readiness Gate)
- Step 9 — runs after all specialist reviews, before scoring
- Critical findings → NOT READY
- High findings → require remediation before production
- Missing required tags = governance failure
- Missing evidence ≠ compliant

## Output
- Prioritize security findings
- Merge duplicates (combined evidence, strongest severity)
- Tag evidence: Observed / Inferred / Missing Evidence / Contradictory Evidence
